# Heart Disease Risk Predictor

A machine learning app that predicts heart disease risk based on patient health data.

🔗 **Live demo:** https://heart-disease-predicto.streamlit.app/

## What it does
Predicts whether a patient is at risk of heart disease using 13 clinical features 
(age, cholesterol, blood pressure, etc.) and a trained Random Forest classifier.

## Key finding: data leakage discovery
The commonly-used 1025-row version of this dataset on Kaggle contains 723 duplicate 
rows, causing severe data leakage when split into train/test sets (inflating AUC to 
0.98–1.00). After removing duplicates (down to 302 rows) and re-evaluating, realistic 
performance was:

| Model | Precision | Recall | F1 | AUC |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Logistic Regression | 0.79 | 0.79 | 0.79 | 0.86 |
| Gradient Boosting | 0.88 | 0.73 | 0.80 | 0.88 |
| Random Forest | 0.90 | 0.77 | 0.83 | 0.91 |

Random Forest was selected as the final model based on AUC, though Logistic 
Regression's higher recall is worth considering given that false negatives 
(missed at-risk patients) are more costly than false positives in this context.

## Tech stack
Python, pandas, scikit-learn, Streamlit

## Run locally
\`\`\`
pip install -r requirements.txt
streamlit run app.py
\`\`\`

## Dataset
UCI Heart Disease dataset (via Kaggle)